@brandonmcd do you have a rough count? I feel like per competition we were down to 2 major repairs on swerve modules at our last off-season. Wheel tread replacement is just part of the usual wear and tear.

The gears in the Max Swerve did not hold up as well as I’d like for a full season, but they would make it through a full competition no problem. The Encoders were the weak point for us. We broke plastic housings on the Hex through bore encoders and that essentially makes it useless. Those are relatively cheap, but can be hard to come by in stock sometimes so get em while you can and bring spares.

If we could find a more robust encoder I’d switch.
